      "type": "articles",
      "specificArticles": [
        {
          "textContent": "Here is one of the biggest open pit from Europe. How does it looks like and what are the consequences? Let's hit the road... From the Historic Center we head to the the 'Tăul Mare' Lake. Once we get here you still have to climb a little until you will reach the Copper Open Pit - Rosia Poieni. The open pit looks like dessert: dry soil, no vegetables, a shaved mountain and rusty huge machines. Get back on the asphalted road until you meet an unpaved road on the left which will lead you through some traditional villages with an authentic charm: Muntari, Poiana and Vința. Once you will see a big lake with powerful colors of red and blue, you reached the waste lake Geamana. <b>The below indications represents the two way length and time.</b>  The trail is on unpaved roads and is perfect for hiking or mountain bikes. The road from Cooper Open Pit to Geamana is quite long, so if you want, you can get back at Casa Petri and go to 'Geamana' by car on asphalted road.",
